Package Required:

- cmake
- zlib
- boost libraries (at least version 1.44)
- google-sparse-hash

How to build the application:

$ cd gam-ngs
$ mkdir build
$ cd build
$ cmake ..
$ make

########################
USAGE
########################

------------------------
BLOCK CONSTRUCTION
------------------------

$ gam-ngs blocks <BAM Master CoordinateSorted> <BAM Master ReadNameSorted> <BAM Slave CoordinateSorted> <BAM Slave ReadNameSorted> <Min Block Size> <Output.filename>

where <Min Block Size> is the number of reads supporting a block (lower values imply longer computation time).
This command outputs the file <Output FileName>.blocks.

------------------------
MERGE
------------------------

$ gam-ngs merge <Input.blocks> <Min Block Size> <BAM Master CoordinateSorted> <BAM Slave CoordinateSorted> <Master FASTA> <Slave FASTA> <Output.filename> <Threads>

where:
- <Input.blocks> is the blocks file created with the previous command.
- <Min Block Size> specifies the minimum number of reads a block must have.

It will output the following files: 
- Output.filename.fasta: output sequence. 
- Output.filename.pctgs: description on how the contigs in pctgs.fasta are built.
- Output.filename.unused: slave contigs which were not used.